  "text": "The endoreplication cell cycle or endocycle is a variation of the normal mitotic cell cycle, in which cells increase their genomic DNA content without dividing. How the transition from the mitotic cycle to the endocycle is regulated is not well understood. Drosophila oogenesis provides an excellent system in which to study this transition [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
